The paper discusses the algorithms and game-theoretic aspects of sponsored search advertising, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR) and online advertising. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of optimization and statistical estimation techniques, which are commonly used in machine learning and data science, suggesting cs.DS and cs.LG as likely sub-categories. The game-theoretic aspects of the auction process suggest cs.GT as a likely sub-category, and the use of market mechanisms and pricing strategies suggest cs.EC as a possible sub-category.
